               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180114-192-person1309">
                  JOHN 
                  SHAW
               <interp inst="t18180114-192-person1309" type="surname" value="SHAW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-192-person1309" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-192-person1309" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am constable of Aldgate. On the 26th of December I was coming down North-East-passage, and saw the prisoner, and another man-the man charged him with stealing the handkerchiefs, and wanted him to return - He refused; I took him back to Mr. Brown's, when Mrs. Page came and said he was one of the men. The young man took me round where he had followed the prisoner, and showed me by the dock wall, where, he said, he had dropped the handkerchiefs. I found them there.</p>
               <p>JAMES WHEELHOUSE. I am shopman to Messrs. 
